    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is offset by the conservative acceptance bounds applied to output comparison and the large sample size. The validation evidence, drawn from a comprehensive survey of published compression-bending datasets for analogous constructs, demonstrates that FEA predictions fall within acceptance bounds across all three QoIs. Overall credibility is judged sufficient for a Medium model risk, Medium consequence COU.",
